The Washington womens rowing team concluded its season Sunday on Lake Natoma in Gold River Calif. by taking second place in the varsity four and third place in the second varsity races at the NCAA championships PERIOD

 head coach Conor Bullis told GoHuskies.com PERIOD 

In the varsity four Grand Finals the UW had the lead up until the last 500meters when a strong push from California pushed the Golden Bears ahead PERIOD The Huskies came in second place with a time of . pERIOD

The UW took the lead at the 1000meter mark in the second varsity but were passed by Cal and Ohio State with 250meters left in the race PERIOD The Huskies took third in . pERIOD

The varsity eight competed in the Petite Finals and earned second place and placing eighth overall PERIOD The UW finished second to Texas in its heat earning its fastest time of the weekend at . pERIOD

The Huskies rounded out the top five with  points PERIOD Cal claiming the national title with a total of  from todays competition PERIOD
